HEADWORD: entangled
<hw>entangled</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>in a confused mass.
Contrasted with <ant>untangled</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>afoul(postnominal), foul, fouled</stype>; <stype>knotted,
snarled, snarly</stype>; <stype>matted</stype>;
<stype>rootbound</stype>; <stype>intertwined</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tangled.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>deeply involved especially in something problematic;
<as>as, <ex>entangled</ex> in the conflict</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> embroiled.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>constrained by or as if by a convoluted rope or net;
